The (Nigerian Society of Engineers) NES Oluyole branch has commended the staff of Oyo State Fire Service operation units for the recent feat as regards Ayede Transmission Station fire outbreak containment. This is as it gave special recognition to some of the staff with uncommon zeal to work without adequate PPE, most importantly the female. Led by the branch chairman, Engineer Abdulrasaq Jimoh, the NSE paid a courtesy visit to the Oyo State Fire Service on Tuesday, February 11. Responding, the Deputy Director, Oyo State Fire Service, Mr O. Adewuyi, thanked the NSE Oluyole branch for the august visit. Why many fail English, Mathematics  examinations —WAEC WIPO is beneficial to Nigeria Need to stop pressurising young people into marriage On bomb blast in Ekiti He said the agency was abandoned by previous administrations in the state. ALSO READ: Oyo govt sacks Oke-Ogun poly management, proscribes butchers’ unions He, however, stated that the Oyo State government has secured five more fire-fighting trucks that are yet to be branded, noting that those were the ones used to combat the recent fire outbreak at Ayede Transmission Station. He added that the procurement process of 10 modern vehicles is on top gear. He enjoined the engineers and the entire public to intensify efforts in advocacy against fire disasters. On the NSE entourage were Engineer Wale Ojoawo, (Vice-Chairman), Engineer Tobi Busari, MNSE (General Secretary), Engineer Samson Ganiyu Okunlola, (ex-officio 1) and a host of others. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE.